citeinfo.title: Ontario County Building Footprints
citeinfo.othercit: This data is updated regularly as new buildings are constructed.

pubinfo.pubplace: Information Services, 70 Ontario Street, Canandaigua, NY 14424

descript.abstract: This polygon vector dataset represents the 2D outline of buildings located in Ontario County, New York State. The features were created though a combination of sources, including LiDAR, orthoimagery, and georereferenced survey maps. Attribution includes specifications for the respective building and tax parcel where the structure is located.
descript.purpose: This polygon vector dataset represents the 2D outline of buildings located in Ontario County, New York State. The information is intended for general reference to support mapping, visualization and analysis.

idinfo.accconst: Data must be formally requested from the Ontario County GIS Program
idinfo.useconst: This data set must not be used, copied in any manner, or transferred in whole or part to a third party or used in any secondary publications or other documents generated unless explicitly given permission by Ontario County. If such permission is granted, the recipient must clearly and fully reference this metadata documentation and credit Ontario County as the source on any secondary works or publications using the transmitted data. There may be instances where the County may not share its data, such as when information is sensitive or is still under development and therefore not ready for general distribution.This data is provided “AS IS”. It is computer-generated using information either acquired or provided to Ontario County from various sources and is intended only for general reference. While the County endeavors to include reliable data for the stated purpose, transmitted data are not intended for and should not be used to establish boundaries, lines, locations of objects or to provide other information typically needed for construction, excavation or any other purpose when engineered drawings/plans or surveys are (1) required by law; (2) required for any legal document; or (3) needed to assure accuracy and/or that certain standards are met. GIS DATA AND DERIVITIVE MAPS ARE NOT SURVEYS!This disclaimer applies to both individual use of the data and aggregate use with other data.

attr.attrdef: Number of physical address. NOTE: For mulit-building complexes (e.g., Mobile Home Park, apartment buildings, etc.) there may be a single address (number, street) assigned to the complex. This is often the main office, manager's residence, or simply the primary entrance to the complex. Consequently, there may be many buildings sharing the same physical address (but assigned different building name/number, floor, and/or unit ID).
